you go out of your way

15:17.250 --> 15:18.551
to pretend that I'm not
even in the room;

15:18.585 --> 15:21.221
that David is the only
one who exists.

15:21.254 --> 15:24.124
Look, I get that you love him;
he's your son.

15:24.157 --> 15:26.326
But I think when
you left your husband,

15:26.359 --> 15:28.228
you were so desperate
for the love of a man

15:28.261 --> 15:29.229
that you latched
onto the only one

15:29.262 --> 15:30.730
you knew would never leave you

15:30.763 --> 15:32.565
and you turned your little boy
into your little boyfriend.

15:32.599 --> 15:35.835
I guess, if we're playing
amateur psychologist--

15:35.868 --> 15:38.171
how come I've never
met your mother, Bryan?

15:38.205 --> 15:40.907
I know you haven't talked
to her since your dad died.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.343
You never call her,
you don't visit.

15:43.376 --> 15:46.146
Does she even know
you're having a baby?

15:46.179 --> 15:47.981
(quietly):
Wow.

15:48.015 --> 15:51.251
I guess you need to work out
your own mommy issues,

15:51.284 --> 15:53.686
and stop taking your crap
out on me.

15:56.223 --> 15:57.624
So what do you want to do?

15:57.657 --> 15:59.859
Do you want to go to dinner,
maybe see a movie?

15:59.892 --> 16:02.595
I feel so good,
I could listen to live jazz.

16:02.629 --> 16:06.533
Yeah, Jane, no offense,
but I don't want to date you,

16:06.566 --> 16:07.834
I just want to bang you.

16:07.867 --> 16:09.702
Bang me?!
Yeah.

16:09.736 --> 16:10.870
Is that what this was?

16:10.903 --> 16:12.439
(groaning):
Oh, boy.

16:12.472 --> 16:14.541
This is what drives me
nuts about older women.

16:14.574 --> 16:16.943
You think that you can go out
and get laid,

16:16.976 --> 16:18.778
and not get emotionally
attached, but you can't.

16:18.811 --> 16:20.780
You just have to turn it
into a relationship.

16:20.813 --> 16:22.949
Oh, don't flatter yourself, bud.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.884
If I was looking
for a relationship,

16:24.917 --> 16:26.486
I imagine I'd aim
a little bit higher

16:26.519 --> 16:28.288
than a vitamin salesman.

16:28.321 --> 16:30.057
Yeah, well, I'd like to imagine
that this was 1980,

16:30.090 --> 16:31.291
and you were still super-hot,

16:31.324 --> 16:32.692
then I wouldn't have
to close my eyes

16:32.725 --> 16:33.693
and pretend I'm banging

16:33.726 --> 16:34.794
a 22-year-old version of you.

16:34.827 --> 16:37.697
Is that what you were thinking?

16:37.730 --> 16:40.167
No, I was really thinking,
"Wow, I'm such a lucky guy

16:40.200 --> 16:42.969
to be screwing a woman who was
alive before computers!"

16:43.002 --> 16:45.472
I wouldn't have given you
the time of day when I was 22.

16:45.505 --> 16:47.374
Exactly.

16:47.407 --> 16:48.841
But look at what
you gave me now.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.446
You know you're fat, right?

16:54.681 --> 16:56.449
(door slams)

17:02.622 --> 17:03.890
Here we are--

17:03.923 --> 17:06.025
wild Pacific salmon
with wasabi crème fraiche.

17:06.059 --> 17:08.195
Oh, my gosh,
it looks amazing.

17:08.228 --> 17:09.929
The center belly section
is the most flavorful.

17:09.962 --> 17:11.531
I want my son
to have it.

17:11.564 --> 17:12.699
Of course you do.

17:12.732 --> 17:14.901
Mom...

17:15.735 --> 17:16.803
Enjoy it, son.

17:21.808 --> 17:23.676
Wow, Frances.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.945
The only thing I'd do different
is bread it, fry it

17:25.978 --> 17:27.847
and add tartar sauce,
but other than that,

17:27.880 --> 17:28.848
it looks really good.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.117
Well, Shania said
she wanted

17:30.150 --> 17:32.852
authentic California cuisine,
and lucky for her,

17:32.885 --> 17:35.522
we have a four-star chef
in the house.

17:35.555 --> 17:37.190
And that's the last thing
on my bucket list.

17:37.224 --> 17:39.126
I guess I can go
back to Ohio.

17:39.159 --> 17:41.228
Oh, thank you.

17:41.261 --> 17:42.895
Yeah.

17:48.435 --> 17:49.736
(coughs)

17:49.769 --> 17:52.205
You okay?
What's the matter, honey?
You okay?

17:52.239 --> 17:54.641
I ate a glob of green pudding.
Fire, fire in my mouth!

17:54.674 --> 17:56.042
Oh!
Oh!

17:56.075 --> 17:57.244
Oh, my God, the wasabi.
The wasabi!

17:57.277 --> 17:58.745
Oh, my God, here,
have some water.
Take some water.

17:58.778 --> 18:00.747
I'm gonna barf.
Okay.

18:00.780 --> 18:02.982
Okay, uh, please use
the housekeeper's toilet.

18:03.015 --> 18:04.584
Got it!
Or any of the ones

18:04.617 --> 18:07.053
with the vintage Malibu tile.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.755
Well, I hope she's good.

18:08.788 --> 18:10.056
Laverne? Shirley?

18:10.089 --> 18:11.057
Doesn't she knock?

18:11.090 --> 18:13.226
Where are the people I like?

18:13.260 --> 18:15.094
Shania ate a glob of wasabi,
and now she's throwing up.

18:15.128 --> 18:16.829
And Goldie is mopping
her tiny face

18:16.863 --> 18:18.097
with Frette hand towels

18:18.131 --> 18:19.832
like they're very, very
expensive Kleenex.

18:19.866 --> 18:21.601
I feel terrible.

18:21.634 --> 18:22.935
Oh, no, don't.
Shania is just fine.

18:22.969 --> 18:24.937
You know, she said it was
as delicious coming back up

18:24.971 --> 18:26.105
as it was going down.

18:26.139 --> 18:27.140
(laughter)

18:27.174 --> 18:28.575
That kid is amazing.
She's fearless.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.076
I know.
JANE:
Fearless?!

18:30.109 --> 18:32.579
Let me tell you something--
fear is good!

18:32.612 --> 18:34.414
And you should
feel terrible

18:34.447 --> 18:37.784
with your crappy fish and
your idiotic ideas about life.

18:37.817 --> 18:39.619
They hurt people's feelings.

18:39.652 --> 18:41.354
And their stomachs.

18:41.388 --> 18:43.190
Nana, Shania is
living her life.

18:43.223 --> 18:45.458
She's nine years old
and made a list of

18:45.492 --> 18:47.460
all the things she wanted
to do and guess what?

18:47.494 --> 18:48.628
She did them.

18:48.661 --> 18:49.962
Can you say the
same thing?

18:49.996 --> 18:51.764
I can't.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.866
People aren't always
supposed to do everything
they think they should do.

18:53.900 --> 18:55.435
It's what separates us
from the animals.

18:55.468 --> 18:57.470
And the native Hawaiians.

18:57.504 --> 19:01.974
Well... all I know is Shania
will never forget today.

19:02.008 --> 19:03.443
So, thank you.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.645
I don't regret
the things I've done.

19:05.678 --> 19:08.047
Only the things
I wanted to do,

19:08.080 --> 19:09.416
and never did.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.488
Hey, there she is.

19:15.522 --> 19:17.123
I feel much better now.

19:17.156 --> 19:19.326
Sorry about your rug.

19:19.359 --> 19:20.360
And your dog.

19:20.393 --> 19:21.661
Ooh.
(dog barks)

19:21.694 --> 19:26.333
Well, you know, if you break
open a capsule of vitamin E,

19:26.366 --> 19:29.068
and you dab just a little
bit of the gel down there,

19:29.101 --> 19:30.803
you'll be amazed how intense
the sensation will be.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.805
JANE:
Paul, what are you
doing here?

19:32.839 --> 19:34.907
I thought it was
your daughter's birthday.

19:34.941 --> 19:37.244
Uh... daughter?

19:37.277 --> 19:39.412
She's only one.
She probably won't remember.

19:39.446 --> 19:41.848
No, no, no, no, don't...

19:43.216 --> 19:45.017
Oh, thanks a lot.

19:45.051 --> 19:46.653
No, thank you. A lot.

19:46.686 --> 19:49.656
For teaching me that it's
never too late to start my life.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.424
You ready, babe?
Yeah.

19:51.458 --> 19:53.693
No regrets.

20:00.767 --> 20:01.768
Well, you can breathe again.

20:01.801 --> 20:03.570
Mom is on her
way back to Napa.

20:03.603 --> 20:05.705
Look, I'm not saying we're
gonna be best friends

20:05.738 --> 20:07.707
anytime soon but...

20:07.740 --> 20:09.509
she did make me feel very good
at dinner tonight.

20:09.542 --> 20:10.877
And if I'm being honest,

20:10.910 --> 20:12.779
she might be a slightly
better cook than I am.

20:12.812 --> 20:15.382
But if we ever have that
pissing contest, it is on.

20:15.415 --> 20:17.049
I'm going to bed.
You coming?

20:17.083 --> 20:19.051
I'll be right up.
There's something I have to do.

20:19.085 --> 20:20.152
Okay.

20:39.672 --> 20:41.674
(line ringing)

20:44.176 --> 20:45.312
WOMAN:
Hello?

20:45.345 --> 20:48.348
Hey, Mom, it's me.

20:54.854 --> 20:56.222
Come on, Shania!
Really hit it, Shania.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.291
Oh, come on! Oh!
Yeah!

20:58.325 --> 20:59.459
Wowie, we-wah!

20:59.492 --> 21:00.627
That looks fun.
Whoo! Arriba!

21:00.660 --> 21:01.794
That's good, baby.

21:01.828 --> 21:03.863
GOLDIE:
That's cheating! Whoa!

21:05.465 --> 21:08.067
Oh, my gosh!
Bryan, stop it!

21:08.100 --> 21:10.136
Whoa! Calm down.

21:11.938 --> 21:14.240
Wow! Bryan,
you're so strong!

21:14.273 --> 21:15.675
Candy!

21:15.708 --> 21:16.809
Oh, goody!

21:16.843 --> 21:17.910
